Dialogue: 1,0:02:07.86,0:02:14.58,1080CN,,0,0,0,,然而，44年前，1973年6月30日
Dialogue: 2,0:02:07.86,0:02:14.58,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Ocean. However a little over 44 years ago on June the 30th 1973 the longest total
Dialogue: 1,0:02:14.58,0:02:18.84,1080CN,,0,0,0,,人们预测到了千年一遇的日全食
Dialogue: 2,0:02:14.58,0:02:18.84,1080EN,,0,0,0,,solar eclipse in a thousand years was predicted to occur with a maximum of
Dialogue: 1,0:02:18.84,0:02:24.75,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最长持续时间7分4秒，横穿整个撒哈拉沙漠
Dialogue: 2,0:02:18.84,0:02:24.75,1080EN,,0,0,0,,seven minutes and four seconds of totality over Saharan Africa. This
Dialogue: 1,0:02:24.75,0:02:30.39,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这次特殊的天象遇到了另一个特殊的事件
Dialogue: 2,0:02:24.75,0:02:30.39,1080EN,,0,0,0,,extraordinary astronomic event coincided with another fortunate circumstance the
Dialogue: 1,0:02:30.39,0:02:34.86,1080CN,,0,0,0,,世界上第一款超音速客机——协和式客机的研发工作
Dialogue: 2,0:02:30.39,0:02:34.86,1080EN,,0,0,0,,world's first supersonic airliner Concorde was nearing the end of its
Dialogue: 1,0:02:34.86,0:02:40.47,1080CN,,0,0,0,,非常顺利并接近尾声。1972年英法两国科学家
Dialogue: 2,0:02:34.86,0:02:40.47,1080EN,,0,0,0,,successful test program. In 1972 British and French scientists recognized a
Dialogue: 1,0:02:40.47,0:02:45.48,1080CN,,0,0,0,,得到了这次千载难逢的机会，他们可以乘坐超音速飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:02:40.47,0:02:45.48,1080EN,,0,0,0,,special opportunity for this Eclipse the path of totality would travel at speeds
Dialogue: 1,0:02:45.48,0:02:51.18,1080CN,,0,0,0,,以两马赫的速度追逐月球的影子
Dialogue: 2,0:02:45.48,0:02:51.18,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which could be matched by Concorde just above Mach 2. By flying one of the
Dialogue: 1,0:02:51.18,0:02:55.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,协和客机原型机之一向南飞行进入月球阴影，上面的科学家们
Dialogue: 2,0:02:51.18,0:02:55.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,prototype airliners South to join the part of the moon shadow, scientists
Dialogue: 1,0:02:55.62,0:03:00.15,1080CN,,0,0,0,,可以观察超过70分钟的日全食，是从地面最长
Dialogue: 2,0:02:55.62,0:03:00.15,1080EN,,0,0,0,,would be able to observe the Eclipse from over 70 minutes, 10 times longer
Dialogue: 1,0:03:00.15,0:03:04.83,1080CN,,0,0,0,,观测时间的十倍。法国天文学家Pierre Léna首先
Dialogue: 2,0:03:00.15,0:03:04.83,1080EN,,0,0,0,,than the longest on the ground. Pierre Léna a French astronomer pitched the
Dialogue: 1,0:03:04.83,0:03:09.06,1080CN,,0,0,0,,向协和式客机飞行员提出了这个想法，飞行员之后又向
Dialogue: 2,0:03:04.83,0:03:09.06,1080EN,,0,0,0,,idea to one of a Concorde test pilots who then suggested the possibility to
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.06,0:03:13.59,1080CN,,0,0,0,,他的老板说了这事，老板听了感觉一颗赛艇
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.06,0:03:13.59,1080EN,,0,0,0,,his bosses at aérospatiale, the French state-owned operator of the
Dialogue: 1,0:03:13.59,0:03:18.78,1080CN,,0,0,0,,认为这是个非常好的，向世人展示
Dialogue: 2,0:03:13.59,0:03:18.78,1080EN,,0,0,0,,prototype jet. The opportunity was warmly received as it was an opportunity to
Dialogue: 1,0:03:18.78,0:03:23.61,1080CN,,0,0,0,,他们最新款超音速客机的机会。然而这次任务还需要面对一些
Dialogue: 2,0:03:18.78,0:03:23.61,1080EN,,0,0,0,,show off the unique capabilities of the new aircraft. The mission posed some
Dialogue: 1,0:03:23.61,0:03:27.95,1080CN,,0,0,0,,技术上的挑战，因为日食发生的位置几乎在飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:03:23.61,0:03:27.95,1080EN,,0,0,0,,technical challenges however, because the eclipse would appear almost directly
Dialogue: 1,0:03:27.95,0:03:32.64,1080CN,,0,0,0,,的正上方，所以飞机的天花板上装了特制的石英舷窗
Dialogue: 2,0:03:27.95,0:03:32.64,1080EN,,0,0,0,,overhead, specialized quartz portholes had to be installed in the roof of the
Dialogue: 1,0:03:32.64,0:03:36.84,1080CN,,0,0,0,,可以承受超音速飞行的压强与高温
Dialogue: 2,0:03:32.64,0:03:36.84,1080EN,,0,0,0,,plane able to withstand the extreme pressure and heat of supersonic flight.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:36.84,0:03:42.23,1080CN,,0,0,0,,另外，所有科学设备都要定制、检查
Dialogue: 2,0:03:36.84,0:03:42.23,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In addition all scientific instruments had to be checked and modified to remove
Dialogue: 1,0:03:42.23,0:03:47.12,1080CN,,0,0,0,,减少一切短路的危险，防止加压客舱内发生火灾
Dialogue: 2,0:03:42.23,0:03:47.12,1080EN,,0,0,0,,any risk of short-circuit that might cause a fire in the pressurized cabin. In
Dialogue: 1,0:03:47.12,0:03:52.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,1973年2月，任务正式批准，五个团队分别来自
Dialogue: 2,0:03:47.12,0:03:52.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,February 1973 the flight was given the official go-ahead and five teams of
Dialogue: 1,0:03:52.50,0:03:56.58,1080CN,,0,0,0,,英法美三国的科学家们登上了协和式客机
Dialogue: 2,0:03:52.50,0:03:56.58,1080EN,,0,0,0,,scientists were chosen from Britain France and America to fill Concorde cabin
Dialogue: 1,0:03:56.58,0:04:01.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,上面有各种观察仪器。1973年6月30日早
Dialogue: 2,0:03:56.58,0:04:01.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,with a variety of observational experiments. On the morning of June 30th
Dialogue: 1,0:04:01.33,0:04:06.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,飞机从大加那利岛起飞
Dialogue: 2,0:04:01.33,0:04:06.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,1973 the supersonic airliner took off from Gran Canaria and turned to
Dialogue: 1,0:04:06.20,0:04:10.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,切入毛里塔尼亚上空的阴影区。之后一直跟着
Dialogue: 2,0:04:06.20,0:04:10.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,intercept the racing shadow of a moon over Mauritania. There they followed it
Dialogue: 1,0:04:10.81,0:04:15.08,1080CN,,0,0,0,,阴影横穿撒哈拉，直到飞机最后不得不在为数不多的机场中
Dialogue: 2,0:04:10.81,0:04:15.08,1080EN,,0,0,0,,across the Sahara until they had to land at one of the few airports which had the
Dialogue: 1,0:04:15.08,0:04:20.02,1080CN,,0,0,0,,的乍得降落。任务圆满成功
Dialogue: 2,0:04:15.08,0:04:20.02,1080EN,,0,0,0,,stopping distance that Concorde required in Chad. The mission was a success
Dialogue: 1,0:04:20.02,0:04:26.12,1080CN,,0,0,0,,协和001航班总共观察到74分钟、有史以来在地球上持续时间最长
Dialogue: 2,0:04:20.02,0:04:26.12,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Concorde 001 observed 74 minutes of totality, the longest ever observation of
Dialogue: 1,0:04:26.12,0:04:31.61,1080CN,,0,0,0,,的日全食。这个记录一直保持到今天而且很难
Dialogue: 2,0:04:26.12,0:04:31.61,1080EN,,0,0,0,,a solar eclipse from Earth. This record still stands today and is unlikely to be
Dialogue: 1,0:04:31.61,0:04:37.66,1080CN,,0,0,0,,再被打破，因为如今已经没有飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:04:31.61,0:04:37.66,1080EN,,0,0,0,,broken anytime soon if ever this is because currently there are no aircraft
Dialogue: 1,0:04:37.66,0:04:42.35,1080CN,,0,0,0,,能飞这么快、这么远。即使有一些军机
Dialogue: 2,0:04:37.66,0:04:42.35,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that can fly fast enough for long enough. Even though there are military jets that
Dialogue: 1,0:04:42.35,0:04:46.85,1080CN,,0,0,0,,可以飞这么快，但它们超音速下航程没有协和那么长
Dialogue: 2,0:04:42.35,0:04:46.85,1080EN,,0,0,0,,can fly faster they don't have the long-distance endurance of Concorde at
Dialogue: 1,0:04:46.85,0:04:52.85,1080CN,,0,0,0,,飞机内也没有那么大空间放科学设备。1999年三架协和客机
Dialogue: 2,0:04:46.85,0:04:52.85,1080EN,,0,0,0,,supersonic speed and they don't have the room for the equipment. In 1999 three Concordes,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:52.85,0:04:57.80,1080CN,,0,0,0,,——一架来自法国、一架来自英国——载着乘客而不是科学家
Dialogue: 2,0:04:52.85,0:04:57.80,1080EN,,0,0,0,,one French and two British flew filled with tourists instead of scientists and
Dialogue: 1,0:04:57.80,0:05:01.91,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在欧洲的一次日全食发生时追逐影子一段时间
Dialogue: 2,0:04:57.80,0:05:01.91,1080EN,,0,0,0,,chased the moons shadow for a short period of time during an eclipse over
Dialogue: 1,0:05:01.91,0:05:06.59,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但之后的“日全食之旅”在2000年7月发生的
Dialogue: 2,0:05:01.91,0:05:06.59,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Europe. However further Concorde Eclipse tours were canceled after the crash of
Dialogue: 1,0:05:06.59,0:05:12.14,1080CN,,0,0,0,,协和4590航班坠毁事故之后就都取消了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:06.59,0:05:12.14,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Concorde flight 4590 from Paris in July 2000. The original
Dialogue: 1,0:05:12.14,0:05:16.25,1080CN,,0,0,0,,之前那架改装过的协和客机还可以在法国巴黎北部
Dialogue: 2,0:05:12.14,0:05:16.25,1080EN,,0,0,0,,modified Concorde can still be seen in its special livery of the Air and Space
Dialogue: 1,0:05:16.25,0:05:21.83,1080CN,,0,0,0,,勒布尔歇航空航天博物馆里看到。如今太阳的研究
Dialogue: 2,0:05:16.25,0:05:21.83,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Museum the Le Bourget , north of Paris in France. Today solar research is done
Dialogue: 1,0:05:21.83,0:05:26.21,1080CN,,0,0,0,,主要是由像SOHO（太阳和日球层探测器）这样的探测器完成的
Dialogue: 2,0:05:21.83,0:05:26.21,1080EN,,0,0,0,,mostly by dedicated space satellites like Soho for Solar and Heliospheric
Dialogue: 1,0:05:26.21,0:05:31.64,1080CN,,0,0,0,,它能使用LASCO（大角度分光日冕观测仪）
Dialogue: 2,0:05:26.21,0:05:31.64,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Observatory which creates its own artificial Eclipse with the LASCO or large
Dialogue: 1,0:05:31.64,0:05:36.53,1080CN,,0,0,0,,“创造出”日食，这使得像1973年协和客机那样在地球上观测
Dialogue: 2,0:05:31.64,0:05:36.53,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Angle and Spectrometric Cronograph Instrument making airborne observations
Dialogue: 1,0:05:36.53,0:05:42.32,1080CN,,0,0,0,,日食显得没有那么有意义了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:36.53,0:05:42.32,1080EN,,0,0,0,,much less significant than in the days of Concorde flight of 1973 but it's
Dialogue: 1,0:05:42.32,0:05:49.24,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但作为某种纪念，如前文所说，NASA还是会在日食时派出两架WB-57进行观测
Dialogue: 2,0:05:42.32,0:05:49.24,1080EN,,0,0,0,,legacy will live on in the flight of NASA's twin WB 57 s later this month.
